<plot>The troubled production for _One from the Heart (1982)_(qv) caused a bit of media attention for American Zoetrope Studios (AKA: The Dream Studio) and Francis Ford Coppola in 1982 when Paramount Pictures backed out of the distribution deal for said film. Accompanied by lots of archive footage and news clippings, we learn what brought this on and how it was eventually resolved.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?554303</url></doc>
